Huruma MCA Peter Owere was arrested on Monday after one person was killed during a meeting he convened.The man was reportedly stabbed to death on Sunday after violence erupted during the meeting in Mathare.Several others were wounded in the incident that some said was instigated by the MCA's rival.Three other people were arrested over the incident.They are all being held at Huruma police station and will be charged on Tuesday.Police said they were preparing the charge sheet.More to follow